----
MVC - separation of concerns / facilitates maintenance and troubleshooting /
    - design pattern (best practice)
----

Model - database
View - Gui / html 
Control - ruby code / connections between gui and data / logic

---

DRY - dont repeat yourself

--

convention over configuration

--

REST - maps resources on to the database
     when yuo use GET / PUT / UPDATE / DELETE http commands

--

Gemfile - it contains ALL dependencies for your app ( like package.json in node/ npm )




